title: Reports: Walker to visit Michigan - High School Sports
text:
Maybe Kareem Walker is keeping his options open after all.
Buy this photo CHRIS PEDOTA/STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER Ohio State commitment Kareem Walker reportedly will take an official visit to Michigan this weekend. The DePaul senior – rated the nation’s top running back and verbally committed to Ohio State – will take an official visit to Michigan this weekend, according to reports.
The 6-foot-1, 210-pound Walker has been committed to the Buckeyes since January. But ESPN’s 22nd-ranked overall prospect in the Class of 2016 remains highly sought after.
Of course, Michigan’s new director of recruiting, Chris Partridge, knows a thing or two about Walker, having spent the past few seasons as Paramus Catholic’s head coach.
Walker's teammate, Nebraska commit Quayshon Alexander, also will visit the Wolverines for their game against Northwestern, according to reports.
Walker has offers from Alabama, Arizona State, Clemson, Florida State, Miami, Michigan, Michigan State, Notre Dame, Tennessee, USC and Wisconsin among other schools.
– Staff report
